  "prompt": "How do I apply for someone's civil death certificate?",
  "response": "To apply for a civil death certificate, follow these general steps:\n\n1. Determine the correct jurisdiction\n- Contact the vital records office in the county or state where the person died\n- Each state has slightly different procedures\n\n2. Gather required information\n- Full name of the deceased\n- Date of death\n- Place of death\n- Sometimes, parents' names or other identifying details\n\n3. Choose your application method\n- In-person at the local vital records office\n- By mail\n- Online through official government websites\n- Some states allow third-party requests\n\n4. Prepare necessary documentation\n- Valid government-issued photo ID\n- Proof of relationship (if you're not an immediate family member)\n- Payment for certificate fees (usually $10-$30)\n\n5. Submit your application\n- Complete the official death certificate request form\n- Include all required documentation\n- Pay the required fee\n\n6. Processing time\n- Can range from a few days to several weeks\n- Some jurisdictions offer expedited services for an additional fee\n\nImportant tips:\n- Check specific requirements for the jurisdiction\n- Only certain individuals can typically obtain a death certificate\n- Some states have restrictions on who can request the document",
